This paper deals with the intersection of deep learning and knowledge representation, specifically in the context of RDFS reasoning. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) as another likely sub-category. The use of neural networks for inference and learning falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the use of RDF graphs and datasets falls under cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for generating justifications, which suggests cs.IR as a possible sub-category.
